+# ZPE-Prosody Workstream Plan — 2026-04-23
+
+## Scope
+
+This is a manual workstream plan for the current `ZPE-Prosody` repo state.
+It is not a formal GPD phase plan because this repo does not contain `.gpd/ROADMAP.md` or `.gpd/STATE.md`.
+
+## Current Status
+
+- Repo: `Zer0pa/ZPE-Prosody`
+- Default branch: `main`
+- Local branch: `chore/true-sal-v7-restamp-2026-04-22`
+- Open PRs:
+  - `#27` `reorientation: execute Prosody doc pass + beta-posture + proof-anchor fixes`
+  - `#28` `chore: instantiate SAL v7.0 portfolio-wide`
+- Current local branch has no PR
+- Local working tree is not clean: `README.md` has an unstaged edit
+- Branch delta vs `main`: `LICENSE`, `pyproject.toml`, `docs/market_surface.json`
+- Tests: `make test` passes locally (`7/7`)
+- Public package surface exists: `zpe-prosody==0.1.0`
+
+## Authority Snapshot
+
+- Compression is real: `16.5952×`
+- F0 fidelity is real: `0.8925%`
+- Quality score is strong: `47/50`
+- Commercial lane remains blocked: retrieval `p@5 = 0.3067` vs `0.80` gate
+- Current wedge is therefore narrow: deterministic prosodic feature encoding, not retrieval-led speech intelligence
+
+## Immediate Risks
+
+- Branch topology is messy:
+  - the checked-out branch is a SAL v7 restamp branch
+  - the stronger doc-reorientation work is on a different open PR
+  - local unstaged README edits mean branch state is not ready for additional mixed work
+- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` and `docs/market_surface.json` on the current branch still carry stale posture/drift relative to the better reorientation direction
+- Further work on this branch before branch hygiene will increase merge friction
+
+## Recommended Next Work
+
+### 1. Branch Hygiene First
+
+Objective: get this lane back to one coherent branch/story before new experiments.
+
+Tasks:
+- Decide whether `#27` is the canonical doc baseline
+- Decide whether `#28` is the canonical SAL/license baseline
+- Rebase or restack the active work so the lane has one clean review path
+- Resolve the unstaged `README.md` edit intentionally instead of letting it float
+
+Success condition:
+- one clean working branch
+- no unstaged edits
+- docs and packaging surface aligned on the same branch
+
+Wall clock:
+- `0.5` to `1.0` day
+
+Resources:
+- local Mac CPU only
+
+### 2. Make the Product Decision Explicit
+
+Objective: choose whether Prosody is being advanced as:
+
+- a deterministic prosodic-feature codec with bounded utility, or
+- a retrieval-bearing product that must clear `PRO-C006`
+
+Recommendation:
+- do not blur these
+- if retrieval remains part of the wedge, it becomes the sovereign engineering objective
+- if retrieval is removed from the wedge, update repo posture accordingly and stop spending cycles on rescue theater
+
+Success condition:
+- one written lane decision
+- wedge and engineering plan match
+
+Wall clock:
+- `0.5` day
+
+Resources:
+- local Mac CPU only
+
+### 3. CPU-First Retrieval Rescue Feasibility Pass
+
+Objective: determine whether `PRO-C006` is salvageable without jumping straight to GPU-heavy learned methods.
+
+Tasks:
+- audit current 12-D handcrafted embedding failure modes
+- run a controlled CPU-only comparator sweep:
+  - normalized contour statistics variants
+  - DTW / soft-DTW style contour matching
+  - channel reweighting and voiced-mask handling variants
+  - simple classical baselines on the same evaluation set
+- preserve exact `p@5` comparisons against the current artifact
+
+Success condition:
+- either a credible CPU path to materially better retrieval
+- or a documented no-go that justifies descoping retrieval from the commercial wedge
+
+Wall clock:
+- `2` to `4` days
+
+Resources:
+- CPU pod helpful, not mandatory
+- local Mac can do code + small tests
+- CPU pod preferred for repeated benchmark sweeps and isolation
+
+### 4. GPU Phase Only If CPU Feasibility Clears
+
+Objective: use GPU only if CPU baselines show the wedge is worth rescuing.
+
+Candidate work:
+- learned speech/prosody embeddings
+- SSL/audio representation bake-off
+- transfer-learning experiments for retrieval on emotional/prosodic similarity
+
+Success condition:
+- GPU work is justified by a prior CPU result, not by hope
+
+Wall clock:
+- `3` to `7` days for first meaningful bake-off
+
+Resources:
+- GPU pod required
+
+## Resource Recommendation
+
+### Local Mac
+
+Use for:
+- branch cleanup
+- docs/package alignment
+- light code changes
+- unit tests
+- artifact inspection
+
+### CPU Pod
+
+Use if doing:
+- repeated retrieval benchmark sweeps
+- dataset preprocessing
+- multi-run comparator experiments
+
+Recommendation:
+- useful for the next meaningful Prosody work
+- not strictly required for documentation or branch cleanup
+
+### GPU Pod
+
+Use only if:
+- the decision is to actively rescue retrieval with learned methods
+
+Recommendation:
+- not needed yet
+- premature before the CPU feasibility pass
+
+## Disproportionate Grant / Commercial Advantage
+
+### Grant Advantage
+
+Moderate, if framed correctly:
+- deterministic speech-feature encoding
+- auditable replay
+- reproducible contour packets
+- bounded, honest failure evidence
+
+Weak, if framed as a retrieval product:
+- the lane currently fails on the very metric that would matter
+
+### Commercial Advantage
+
+Current state: limited
+
+Why:
+- compression + fidelity are good
+- retrieval failure blocks the broader wedge
+- no promoted head-to-head comparator story exists
+
+Best commercial angle today:
+- deterministic prosodic feature packet / auditability / reproducibility infrastructure
+
+Best commercial upside path:
+- only if retrieval can be materially improved
+
+## Decision Gate
+
+Recommended order:
+
+1. Clean branch state and restack open work
+2. Make the wedge decision explicit
+3. Run CPU-only retrieval feasibility
+4. Only then decide on GPU
+
+## Recommended Immediate Command Path
+
+- review and resolve the current unstaged `README.md` change
+- choose whether `#27` and `#28` should be merged/restacked
+- if retrieval remains in scope, start a CPU comparator plan next
+
+## Bottom Line
+
+Prosody is technically real but commercially narrow in its current state.
+The highest-value next move is not GPU work. It is branch hygiene plus a hard decision on whether retrieval is being rescued or removed from the wedge.
